						<div class="bio-img">
							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-25-at-9.35.43-PM-150x150.png" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Screenshot-2026-01-25-at-9.35.43-PM-300x300.png 2x" alt="Dobby Gibson" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Dobby Gibson</h4>
												<p>Dobby Gibson is the author of five books of poetry, most recently <em>Hold Everything</em> (Graywolf Press, 2024), which won The Four Quartets Prize from the Poetry Society of America and the T.S. Eliot Foundation. His poems have appeared in <em>American Poetry Review, The New Yorker</em>, and <em>The Paris Review</em>, among many other places. He lives in Saint Paul, Minnesota.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
